### Dexie.Syncable API Reference

Source: https://github.com/dexie/dexie.js/blob/master/addons/Dexie.Syncable/README.md

Comprehensive API documentation for Dexie.Syncable, covering static members, non-static methods, and events for managing database synchronization.

```APIDOC
Static Members:
  Dexie.Syncable.registerSyncProtocol(name: string, protocolInstance: ISyncProtocol)
    Description: Define how to replicate changes with your type of server.

  Dexie.Syncable.Statuses
    Description: Enum of possible sync statuses (e.g., OFFLINE, CONNECTING, ONLINE, ERROR).

  Dexie.Syncable.StatusTexts
    Description: Text lookup for status numbers.

Non-Static Methods and Events (on db.syncable):
  db.syncable.connect(protocol: string, url: string, options: object)
    Description: Create a persistent two-way sync connection with the given URL.

  db.syncable.disconnect(url: string)
    Description: Stop syncing with the given URL but keep revision states until next connect.

  db.syncable.delete(url: string)
    Description: Delete all states and change queue for given URL.

  db.syncable.list()
    Description: List the URLs of each remote node we have a state saved for.

  db.syncable.on('statusChanged')
    Description: Event triggered when sync status changes.

  db.syncable.setFilter(criteria: any[], filter: Function)
    Description: Ignore certain objects from being synced defined by the given filter.

  db.syncable.getStatus(url: string)
    Description: Get sync status for the given URL.

  db.syncable.getOptions(url: string)
    Description: Get the options object for the given URL.
```

